4 The Senate proposes to the House to amend the bill by striking out all after
5 the enacting clause and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
6 Sec. 1. INTENT
7 It is the intent of the General Assembly to ensure that a buyer of real
8 property is on notice regarding the flood risks associated with the purchase of
9 the real property.
10 Sec. 2. 27 V.S.A. § 380 is amended to read:
11 § 380. DISCLOSURE OF INFORMATION; CONVEYANCE OF REAL
12 ESTATE
13 (a) Prior to or as part of a contract for the conveyance of real property, the
14 seller shall provide the buyer with the following information:
15 (1) whether the real property is located in a Federal Emergency
16 Management Agency mapped special flood hazard area; [Repealed.]
17 (2) whether the real property is located in a Federal Emergency
18 Management Agency mapped moderate flood hazard area; [Repealed.]
19 (3) a physical or electronic copy or a digital link of the official flood
20 insurance rate map, as published by the Federal Emergency Management
